efines the scruffy, vernacular field of Downtown music from which so much of the most fertile recent American music has come.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aGeneral. 4aMusic. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh1 aGann, Kyle, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052022982240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093593840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520935938423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520935938/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles